\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "They have notions of fairness. If we violate those\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Okay, okay. " He started action again. "The next question is how. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't care how you do it, " the hologram said. "Just do it\emdash at once!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Hold off, " Marq said. "We'll let you have running time, to integrate your perception space. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "What does that mean?" Voltaire asked. "Artful expression is one thing, jargon another. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "To work out your kinks, " Marq replied dryly.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "So that we can converse?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, " Sybyl said. "At your initiation, not just ours. Don't go for a walk at the same time, though\emdash that requires too much data-shuffling. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "We're trying to hold costs down here, " Marq said, leaning back so he could get a better view of Sybvl's legs.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Well, hurry up, " the Voltaire image said. "Patience is for martyrs and saints, not for men of belles lettres. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The translator rendered all this in present language.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 inserting the audio of ancient, lost words. Knowledge fetchers found the translation and overlaid it for Marq and Sybyl. Still, Marq had left in the slippery, natural acoustics for atmosphere\emdash 
the tenor of the unimaginably distant past.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Just say my name, or Sybyl's, and we'll appear to you in a rectangle rimmed in red. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Must it be red?" The Maid's voice was frail. "Can you not make it blue? Blue is so cool, the color of the sea. Water is stronger than fire, can put fire out. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Stop babbling, " the other hologram snapped. He beckoned to a mechwaiter and said, "That flambe dish, there\emdash put i
t out at once. It's upsetting the Maid. And you two geniuses out there! If you can resurrect the dead, you certainly should be able to change red to blue. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't believe this, " said Sybyl. "A sim? Who does he think he is?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "The voice of reason, " Marq replied. "Francois-Marie Arouet de Voltaire. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Do you think they're ready to see Boker?" Sybyl chewed prettily at her lip. "We agreed to let him into the sim as soon as they were stabilized. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Marq thought. "Let's play it square and linear with him. I'll call. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "We have so much to learn from them!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "True. Who could have guessed that prehistoricals could be such bastards?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 4.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She tried to ignore the sorceress called Sybyl, who claimed to be her creator\emdash as if anyone but the King}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 of Heaven could lay claim to such a feat. She didn't feel like talking to anyone. Events crowded in\emdash  rushed, dense, suffocating. Her choking, pain-shot death still swarmed about her.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 On the dunce's cap\emdash the one they'd set upon her shaven head on that fiery day, the darkest and yet most glorious day of her short life\emdash 
her "crimes" were inscribed in the holy tongue: Heretica, Relapsa, Apostata, Idolater. Black words, soon to ignite.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The learned cardinals and bishops of the foul, English-loving University of Paris, and of the Church\emdash Christ's bride on earth!\emdash had set her living body on fire. All for carrying out the Lord's will
\emdash that the Great and True King should be His minister in France. For that, they had rejected the king's ransom, and sent her to the searing pyre. What then might they not do to this sorceress called Sybyl\emdash 
who, like her, dwelt among men, wore men's attire, and claimed for herself powers that eclipsed those of the Creator Himself?}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Please go away, " she murmured. "I must have silence if I am to hear my voices. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 But neither La Sorciere nor the bearded man in black named Boker\emdash who resembled uncannily the glowering patriarchs on the domed ceiling of the great church at Rouen\emdash would leave her alone.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She implored them, "If you must talk, natter at Monsieur Arouet. That one likes nothing more. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Sacred Maid, Rose of France, " said the bearded one, "was France your world?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "My station in the world, " Joan said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Your planet, I mean. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Planets are in the sky. I was of the earth. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I mean\emdash oh, never mind. " He spoke soundlessly to the woman, Sybyl\emdash "Of the ground? Farmers? Could even prehistoricals be so ignorant?"\emdash apparently thinking she could not read lips, a trick she had
}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 mastered to divine the deliberations of churchly tribunals.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Joan said, "I know what is sufficient to my charge. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
Boker frowned, then rushed on. "Please, hear me out. Our cause is just. The fate of the sacred depends upon our winning to our side many converts. If we are to uphold the vessel of humanity, and time-honored traditions of our very 
identity, we must defeat Secular Skepticism. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She tried to turn away, but the clanking weight of her chains stopped her. "Leave me alone. Although I killed no one, I fought in many combats to assure the victory of France's Great True King. I presided over
 his coronation at Rheims. I was wounded in battle for his sake. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She held up her wrists\emdash for she was now in the foul cell at Rouen, in leg irons and chains. Sybyl had said this would anchor her, be good for her character in some way. As an angel, Sybyl wa
s no doubt correct. Boker began to implore her, but Joan summoned strength to say, "The world knows how I was requited for my pains. I shall wage war no more. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Monsieur Boker turned to the sorceress. "A sacrilege, to keep a great figure in chains. Can't you transport her to some place of theological rest? A cathedral?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Context. Sims need context, " La Sorciere said without sound. Joan found she could read lips with a clarity she had never known. Perhaps this Purgatory improved its charges.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Monsieur Boker clucked. "I am impressed with what you've done, but unless you can make her cooperate, what good is she to us?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You haven't seen her at the summit of her Selfhood. The few historical associations we have been able to decipher claim that she was a 'mesmerizing presence. ' We'll have to bring that out. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Can you not make her smaller? It's }{\fs20 impossible}{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033  to}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 talk to a giant. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The Maid, to her astonishment, shrank b}{\fs20 y}{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033  two-thirds in height.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Monsieur Boker seemed pleased. "Great loan, you misunderstand the nature of the war that lies ahead. Uncountable millennia have passed since your ascension into heaven. You\emdash "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The Maid sat up. "Tell me one thing. Is the king of France a descendant of the English Henry's House of Lancaster? Or is he a Valois, descended from the Great and True King Charles?"}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Monsieur Boker blinked and thought. "I... I think it may be truly said that we Preservers of Our Father's Faith, the party I represent, are in a manner of speaking descendants of your Charles. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The Maid smiled. She knew her voic
es had been heaven-sent, no matter what the bishops said. She'd only denied them when they took her to the cemetery of St. Ouen, and then only for fear of the fire. She'd been right to recant her recantation two days later; the Lancastrian failure to anne
x France confirmed that. If Monsieur Boker spoke for descendants of the House of Valois, despite his clear absence of a noble title, she would hear him out.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Proceed, " she said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Monsieur Boker explained that this place was soon to hold a referendum. (After
 some deliberation with La Sorciere, he advised that loan should think of this place as France, in essence. ) The contest would be between two major parties, Preservers vs. Skeptics. Both parties had agreed to hold a Great Debate between two verbal duelis
ts, to frame the salient question.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "What issue?" the Maid asked sharply.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Whether mechanical beings endowed with artificial intelligence should be built. And if so, should}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 they be allowed full citizenship, with all attendant rights. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The Maid shrugged. "A joke? Only aristocrats and noblemen have rights. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Not anymore, though of course we do have a class system. Now the common lot enjoy rights. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Peasants like me?" the Maid asked. "We?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Monsieur Boker, face a moving flurry of exasperated scowls, turned to La Sorciere. "Must I do everything?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You wanted her as is, " La Sorciere said. "Or, rather, as was. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Monsieur Boker spent two minutes ranting about something he called the Conceptual Shift. This-term meant an apparently theological di
spute about the nature of mechanical artifice. To Joan the answer seemed clear, but then, she was a woman of the fields, not a word artisan.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Why don't you ask your king? One of his counselors? Or one of your learned men?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Monsieur Boker curled his lip, dismissively fanned the air. "Our leaders are pallid! Weak! Rational doormats!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Surely\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You cannot imagine, coming from ancient passion. Intensity and passion are regarded as bad form, out of style. We wished to find intellects with the old fire, the\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No! Oh!" The flames, licking-It was some moments before her breathing calmed and she could shakily listen again.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The great debate between Faith and Reason would be held in the Coliseum of Junin Sector before an audience of 400, 000 souls. The Maid and her o
pponent would appear in holograms, magnified by a factor of thirty. Each citizen would then vote on the question.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Vote?" the Maid inquired.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You wanted her uncorrupted, " La Sorciere said. "You got her. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The Maid listened in silence, forced to absorb millennia in minutes. When Monsieur Boker finished, she said, "I excelled in battle, if only for a brief time, but never in argument. No doubt you know of my fate. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Monsieur Boker looked pained. "The vagueries of the ancients! We have a skimpy historical frame around your, ah, representation\emdash 
no more. We know not what place you lived, but we do know minutiae of events after your\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Death. You can speak of it. I am accustomed to it, as any Christian maiden should be, upon arrival in Purgatory. I know who you two are, as well. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 La Sorciere asked cautiously, "You... do?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Angels! You manifest yourselves as ordinary folk, to calm my fears. Then you set me a task. Even if it involves the roguish, it is a divine mission. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Monsieur Boker nodded slowly, glancing at L
a Sorciere. "From the tatters of data flapping about your Self, we gather that your reputation was restored at hearings held twenty-six years after your death. Those involved in your condemnation repented of their mistake. You were called, in high esteem,
 La Rose de la Loire. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She blinked back wistful tears. "Justice... Had I been skilled in argument, I'd have convinced my inquisitors\emdash those English-loving preachers of the University of Paris!\emdash that I am not a witch. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Monsieur Boker seemed moved. "Even pre-antiquity knew when a holy power was with them. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The Maid laughed, lighthearted. "The Lord's on the side of His Son, and the saints and martyrs, too. But that does not mean they escape failure and death. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "She's right, " La Sorciere said. "Even worlds and galaxies share man's fate. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "We of spirituality need you, " Monsieur Boker pleaded. "We have become too much like our machines. We hold nothing sacred except the smooth functioning of our parts. We know you will ad
dress the question with intensity, yet in simplicity and truth. That is all we ask. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The Maid felt fatigued. She needed solitude, time to reflect. "I must consult with my voices. Will there be only one, or many questions that I must address?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Just one. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
The inquisitors had been far more demanding. They asked many questions, dozens, sometimes the same ones, over and over again. Right answers at Poitiers proved wrong elsewhere. Deprived of food, drink, rest, intimidated by the enforced journey to the cemet
ery, exhausted by the tedious sermon they compelled her to hear, and wracked by terror of the fire, she could not withstand their interrogation.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Does the Archangel Michael have long hair?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Is St. Margaret stout or lean?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Are St. Catherine's eyes brown or blue?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 They trapped her into assigning to voices of the spirit attributions of the flesh. Then they perversely condemned her for confounding sacred spirit with corrupt flesh.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 All had been miasma. And in Purgatory, worse trials could ensue. She could not therefore be certain if this Boker would turn out to be friend or foe.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "What is it?" she wanted to know. "This single question you want me to answer. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "There is universal consensus that man-made intelligences have a kind of brain. The question we want you to answer is whether they have a soul. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Only the Almighty has the power to create a soul. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Monsieur Boker smiled. "We Preservers couldn't agree with you more. Artificial intelligences, unlike us, their creators, have no
 soul. They're just machines. Mechanical contrivances with electronically programmed brains. Only man has a soul. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "If you already know the answer to the question, why do you need me?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "To persuade! First the undecided of Junin Sector, then Trantor, then the Empire!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
The Maid reflected. Her inquisitors had known the answers to the questions they plied her with, too. Monsieur Boker seemed sincere, but then so were those who pronounced her a witch. Monsieur Boker had told her the answer beforehand, one with 
which any sensible person would agree. Still, she could not be sure of his intentions. Not even the crucifix she asked the priest to hold aloft was proof against the }{\fs20 oily}{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033  smoke, the biting flames....}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Well?" asked Monsieur Boker. "Will the Sacred Rose consent to be our champion?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "These people I must convince. Are they, too, descendants of Charles, the Great and True King, of the House of Valois?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 5.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 When Marq strode into Splashes & Sniffs to meet}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 his buddy and coworker Nim, he was surprised to}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 find Nim already there. To judge from Nim's dilated}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 pupils, he'd been there most of the afternoon.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Marq said, "Hitting it hard? Something going on?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Nim shook his head. "Same old Marq, blunt as a}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
