\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She held up her chains, recalling the fur cloak the king himself had placed about he
r shoulders at his coronation in Rouen. She thought of asking for it now, but decided against it. They had made much of her cloak during her trial, accusing her of having a demon-inspired love of luxury; she who, until she won the king over that day she f
irst appeared at court, had felt nothing but coarse burlap against her skin. Her accusers, she had noted, wore black satin and velvet and reeked of perfume.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I'll do what I can, " Madame la Sorciere vowed, "but you must agree not to tell Monsieur Boker. He 
doesn't want you fraternizing with the enemy, but I think it will do you good. Hone your skills for the Great Debate. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 There was a pause\emdash falling, soft clouds\emdash in which the Maid felt as if she had fainted. When she recovered\emdash hard cool surfaces, sudden sharp splashes of brown, green\emdash 
she found herself seated in the Inn of the Two Maggots, once again, surrounded by guests who seemed not to know that she was there.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Armor-plated beings bearing trays and clearing tableware darted am
ong the guests. She looked for Garcon and spotted him gazing at the honey-haired cook, who pretended not to notice. Garcon's longing recalled the way the Maid herself had gazed at statues of St. Catherine and St. Margaret, who had both forsworn men but ad
opted their attire; suspended between two worlds, holy passion above, earthy ardor below. Just as here, with its jarring jargon of numbers and machines, though she knew it for a purgatorial waiting cloister, floating between the worlds.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She suppressed a smile when Monsieur Arouet appeared. He sported a dark, unpowdered wig, though still looked rather old\emdash 
about the age of her father Jacques Dars, thirty plus one or two. His shoulders slumped forward under the weight of many books. }{\fs20 She'd}{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033  only seen books twice,
 during her trials, and though they looked nothing like these, she recoiled at the memory of their power.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Alors, " Monsieur Arouet said, setting the books before her. "Forty-two volumes. My Selected Works. Incomplete but\emdash " he smiled "\emdash for now, it will have to do. What's wrong?"}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Do you mock me? You know I cannot read. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I know. Garcon 213-ADM is going to teach you. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I do not want to learn. All books except the Bible are born of the devil. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Monsieur Arouet threw up his hands and lapsed into curses, violent and intriguing oaths like those her soldiers used when they forgot that she was near. "You must learn how to read. Knowledge is power!"}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "The devil must know a great deal, " she said, careful to let no part of the books touch her.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Monsieur Arouet, exasperated, turned to the sorceress\emdash who appeared to be sitting at a nearby table\emdash 
and said, "Vac! Can't you teach her anything?" Then he turned back to her. "How will you appreciate my brilliance if you can't even read?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I have no use for it. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Ha! Had you been able to read, you'd have }{\fs20 Confounded}{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033  those }{\fs20 idiots}{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033  who sent you to the stake. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "AD teamed men, " she said. "Like you. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No, pucellette, not like me. Not like me at all. " As if it were a serpent, she recoiled from the book he held out. Grinning, he rubb
ed the book all over himself and Gar?on, who was now standing beside the table. "It's harmless\emdash see?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Evil is often invisible, " she murmured.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Monsieur is right, " Gar?on told her. "All the best people read. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Had you been lettered, " Monsieur Arouet sai
d, "you'd have known that your inquisitors had absolutely no right to try you. You were a prisoner of war, seized in battle. Your English captor had no legal right to have your religious views examined by French inquisitors and academics. You pretended to
 believe your voices were divine\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Pretended!" she cried out.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "\emdash and he pretended to believe they were demonic. The English are themselves too tolerant to burn anyone at the stake. They leave such forms of amusement to our countrymen, the French. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Not too tolerant, " the Maid said, "to turn me over to the bishop of Beauvais, claiming I was a witch. " She looked away, unwilling to let him peer in her eyes. "Perhaps I am. I betrayed my own voices. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Voices of conscience, nothing more. The pagan Socrates hea
rd them as well. Everyone does. But it's unreasonable to sacrifice our lives to them, if only because to destroy ourselves on their account is to destroy them, too. " He sucked reflectively on his teeth. "Persons of good breeding betray them as a matter o
f course. " "And we, here?" Joan whispered. He narrowed his eyes. "These... others? The scientists?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "They are spectral. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Like demons? Yet they speak of reason. They have raised a republic of analysis. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "So they say it is. Yet they have asked us to represent what they do not have. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You think them bloodless. " Voltaire twisted his mouth in surprised speculation.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I think we listen to the same 'scientists, ' so we are being tested in the same trial. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I heed voices such as theirs, " Voltaire said defensively. "I, at least, know when to turn my head aside from mindless advice. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Perhaps Monsieur's voices are soft, " Garcon suggested. "Therefore, more easily ignored. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I let them\emdash churchly men!\emdash force me to admit my voices were the devil's, " said the Maid, "when all the while I knew they were divine. Isn't that the act of a demon? A witch?"}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
