\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Your orders, " said Gar$on 213-ADM with a flourish.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He was having difficulty following the arguments between the Maid and the Monsieur on whether beings like himself possessed a soul. Monsieur seemed to believe that no one at all had a soul\emdash 
 which outraged the Maid. They argued with such heat they did not notice the disappearance of the odd ghost presence who usually watched them, a "programmer" of this space.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
Now was Garcon's chance to implore Monsieur to intervene on his behalf and ask his human masters to give him a name. 213-ADM was just a mechfolk code: 2 identified his function, mechwaiter; 13 placed him in this Sector, an
d. ADM stood for Aux Deux Magots. He was sure he'd have a better chance of attracting the honey-haired short-order cook's attention if he had a human name.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Monsieur, Madame. Your orders, please. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "What good is ordering?" Monsieur snapped. Patience, Garcon observed, was not improved by learning. "We cannot taste a thing!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Garcon gestured sympathetically with two of his four hands. He had no experience of human senses except sight, sound, and rudimentary touch, those necessary to perform his job. He would h
ave given anything to taste, to feel; humans seemed to derive such pleasure from it.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The Maid perused the menu and, changing the subject, said, "I'll have my usual. A crust of bread\emdash  I'll try a sourdough baguette crust for a change\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
