\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari saw he had overstepped. What's more, he had nearly exposed psychohistory.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Yet he found it hard to not speak frankly. In his view the humanities and social sciences shrank to specialized branches of bot
h mathematics and biology. History, biography, and fiction were symptoms. Anthropology and sociology together became the sociobiology of a single species. But he could not get a feel for how to include that in the equations. He had spoken out, he saw sudd
enly, because he was frustrated\emdash by his own lack of understanding.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
