He gave the edged stone to Hunker. The pan seemed surprised, but took it. Hari hoped the symbolism of the gesture would penetrate in some fashion, because he had no time left to spend on pan politics. Hunker hefted the 
rock and looked at Ipan. Then he cried in a rolling, powerful voice, tones rich in joy and triumph.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
