\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 THEY KEEP US HERE, KILL PANS, THAT KILLS US. BLAME ON ANIMALS?}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He had better arguments to ba
ck up his case. The slow accumulation of small details in Vaddo's behavior. Suspicions, at least, about the security officer. Dors' tiktok would block the officer from overriding the locks on their immersion capsules, and from tracing the capsule's signal
 to Ipan and Sheelah.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 So they were forced to go into the field. Letting them die in an "accident" while immersed in a pan might just be plausible enough to escape an investigation.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The humans went about their noisy business. They were enough, though, to make his case. Sheelah's eyes narrowed, the big brow scowled.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Dors-the-Defender took over. Where? Sheelah signed.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He had no sign for so abstract an idea, so he scribbled with the stick, AWAY. Indeed, he had no plan.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
