\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I never would have believed a pan could, could... "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I doubt anyone's been immersed this long. Not under such stress, anyway. It all just\emdash well, it came out. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He picked up Vaddo's weapon and studied the mechanism. A standard pistol, silenced. Vaddo had not wanted to awaken the rest of the station. That was 
promising. There should be people here who would spring to their aid. He started toward the building where the station personnel lived.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Wait, what about Vaddo?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I'm going to wake up a doctor. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 They did\emdash but Hari took him into the vessel room first, to work on Ipan. Some patchwork and injections and the doctor said Ipan would be all right. Only then did he show the man Vaddo's body.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The doctor got angry about that, but Hari had a gun. All he had to do was point it. He didn't say anything, just gestured with the gun.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He did not feel like talking and wondered if he ever would again. When you couldn't talk you concentrated more, entered into things. Immersed.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 And in any case, Vaddo had been dead for some time.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Ipan had done a good job. The doctor shook his head at the severe damage.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Alarms were ringing. He got an instant headache. The security officer showed up. He could see from her reaction that she had n
ot been in on the plot. Can't connect it to the Academic Potentate, then, he thought abstractly.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 But how much did that prove? Imperial politics were subtle.... Dors looked at him oddly the whole time. He did not understand why, until he realized that he ha
d not even thought about helping Vaddo first. Ipan was himself, in a sense he knew deeply but could not explain.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 But he understood immediately when Dors wanted to go to the station wall and call to Sheelah. They brought her, too, in from the far wild darkness.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
