Of course, we know some incidental answers. The term "psychohistory" was commonly used in the thirties and appears in the 1934 Webster's Dictionary; Isaac greatly extended its meaning, though. He didn't want to deal with John W. Campbell's not
orious dislike of aliens who might be as clever as we, so his Foundation had none. But it seemed to me there might be more to the matter.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
